  "description": "A survey of non-Western governance frameworks that offer foundational alternatives to the Hohfeldian legal model and state-centric authority structures, including Haudenosaunee confederacy, Anishinaabe clan governance, Ubuntu philosophy, Andean ayllu systems, and Aboriginal Australian kinship governance.",
  "name": "Indigenous Governance Traditions Beyond State Sovereignty",
